    },
    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:1.1",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho anāthapiṇḍiko devaputto bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
          "en": "Standing to one side, the god Anāthapiṇḍika recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:2.1",
          "pli": "“Idañhi taṃ jetavanaṃ, ",
          "en": "“This is indeed that Jeta’s Grove, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:2.2",
          "pli": "isisaṅghanisevitaṃ; ",
          "en": "frequented by the Saṅgha of hermits, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:2.3",
          "pli": "Āvutthaṃ dhammarājena, ",
          "en": "where the King of Dhamma stayed: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:2.4",
          "pli": "pītisañjananaṃ mama. ",
          "en": "it brings me joy! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:3.1",
          "pli": "Kammaṃ vijjā ca dhammo ca, ",
          "en": "Deeds, knowledge, and principle; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:3.2",
          "pli": "sīlaṃ jīvitamuttamaṃ; ",
          "en": "ethical conduct, an excellent livelihood; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:3.3",
          "pli": "Etena maccā sujjhanti, ",
          "en": "by these are mortals purified, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:3.4",
          "pli": "na gottena dhanena vā. ",
          "en": "not by clan or wealth. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:4.1",
          "pli": "Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso, ",
          "en": "That’s why an astute person, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:4.2",
          "pli": "sampassaṃ atthamattano; ",
          "en": "seeing what’s good for themselves, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:4.3",
          "pli": "Yoniso vicine dhammaṃ, ",
          "en": "would examine the teaching rationally, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:4.4",
          "pli": "evaṃ tattha visujjhati. ",
          "en": "and thus be purified in it. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:5.1",
          "pli": "Sāriputtova paññāya, ",
          "en": "Sāriputta has true wisdom, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:5.2",
          "pli": "sīlena upasamena ca; ",
          "en": "ethics, and also peace. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:5.3",
          "pli": "Yopi pāraṅgato bhikkhu, ",
          "en": "Any mendicant who has gone beyond "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:5.4",
          "pli": "etāvaparamo siyā”ti. ",
          "en": "can at best equal him.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:6.1",
          "pli": "Idamavoca anāthapiṇḍiko devaputto. ",
          "en": "This is what the god Anāthapiṇḍika said. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:6.2",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi. ",
          "en": "Then he bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right side, before vanishing right there. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:7.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:7.2",
          "pli": "“imaṃ, bhikkhave, rattiṃ aññataro devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, tonight, a certain glorious god, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, came to me, bowed, stood to one side, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:7.3",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhikkhave, so devaputto mama santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: ",
          "en": "and recited these verses in my presence.” The Buddha then repeated the verses in full. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:8.1",
          "pli": "‘Idañhi taṃ jetavanaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:8.2",
          "pli": "isisaṅghanisevitaṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:8.3",
          "pli": "Āvutthaṃ dhammarājena, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:8.4",
          "pli": "pītisañjananaṃ mama. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:9.1",
          "pli": "Kammaṃ vijjā ca dhammo ca, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:9.2",
          "pli": "sīlaṃ jīvitamuttamaṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:9.3",
          "pli": "Etena maccā sujjhanti, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:9.4",
          "pli": "na gottena dhanena vā. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:10.1",
          "pli": "Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:10.2",
          "pli": "sampassaṃ atthamattano; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:10.3",
          "pli": "Yoniso vicine dhammaṃ, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:10.4",
          "pli": "evaṃ tattha visujjhati. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:11.1",
          "pli": "Sāriputtova paññāya, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:11.2",
          "pli": "sīlena upasamena ca; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:11.3",
          "pli": "Yopi pāraṅgato bhikkhu, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:11.4",
          "pli": "etāvaparamo siyā’ti. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:12.1",
          "pli": "Idamavoca, bhikkhave, so devaputto. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:12.2",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyī”ti. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:13.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:13.2",
          "pli": "“so hi nūna, bhante, anāthapiṇḍiko devaputto bhavissati. ",
          "en": "“Sir, that god must surely have been Anāthapiṇḍika. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:13.3",
          "pli": "Anāthapiṇḍiko gahapati āyasmante sāriputte abhippasanno ahosī”ti. ",
          "en": "For the householder Anāthapiṇḍika was devoted to Venerable Sāriputta.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:13.4",
          "pli": "“Sādhu sādhu, ānanda, yāvatakaṃ kho, ānanda, takkāya pattabbaṃ anuppattaṃ taṃ tayā. ",
          "en": "“Good, good, Ānanda. You’ve reached the logical conclusion, as far as logic goes. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:13.5",
          "pli": "Anāthapiṇḍiko hi so, ānanda, devaputto”ti. ",
          "en": "For that was indeed the god Anāthapiṇḍika.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:13.6",
          "pli": "Anāthapiṇḍikavaggo dutiyo. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:14.1",
          "pli": "Candimaso ca veṇḍu ca, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:14.2",
          "pli": "Dīghalaṭṭhi ca nandano; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:14.3",
          "pli": "Candano vāsudatto ca, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:14.4",
          "pli": "Subrahmā kakudhena ca; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:14.5",
          "pli": "Uttaro navamo vutto, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn2.20:14.6",
          "pli": "Dasamo anāthapiṇḍikoti. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
